JOHANNESBURG - The disciplinary hearing for suspended Eskom boss, Matshela Koko, will resume on Thursday. 
	
	The suspended Eskom boss faces six charges‚ including irregularly awarding of more than R1-billion in tenders to a company in which his stepdaughter had an interest. Two senior Eskom Managers who are also suspended, refused to testify on Saturday. WATCH: Suspended Eskom CEO says the public has a right to know Former Eskom Contract Manager France Hlakudi and Group Capital Executive Abraham Masango say they won't take part in a compromised hearing. Masango's lawyer says his client's willing to testify in an independent hearing against Koko. Eskom's evidence leader Cassim Moosa wrapped up his case due to lack of further witnesses. Koko will give evidence on Thursday. eNCA